== Grave Goods<ref>"Rikuen Old Artifacts Analysis" by Munetada Aoyagi, "Mikumo Site: Minamishouji District," Fukuoka Prefectural Cultural Property Survey Report No. 69, Fukuoka Prefectural Board of Education, 1985.</ref> == '''Jar Burial 1''' * '''Outside the jar''' ** 1 bronze sword ** 1 bronze halberd ** 1 small vermilion-stained jar * '''Inside the jar''' ** 2 bronze spears ** 31 or more bronze mirrors ({{ill|Han-style mirror|lt=Han-style mirror|lt=Han mirrors|ja|前漢鏡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Han mirrors|qq=}}) ** 8 or more fragments of glass bi disks (lapis lazuli) ** 3 glass magatama beads ** Over 60 glass tubular beads ** 8 or more gold-co11er four-leaf decorative fittings ** '''Bronze mirrors''': Sizes range from 27.3 cm to 16.0 cm. Most are [[:en:Inscribed mirror|Linked arc-patterned inscribed band mirrors]], comprising 26 or more specimens.
'''Jar Burial 2''' * 22 or more bronze mirrors (Han mirrors) * 1 glass pendant (possibly reused fragments of a lapis lazuli bi disk) * 13 magatama beads (1 jadeite, 12 glass) * '''Bronze mirrors''': Sizes range from 11.4 cm to 6.0 cm. Most are {{ill|Inscribed mirror|lt=Linked arc-patterned "Sunlight" inscribed mirrors|ja|連弧文「日光」銘鏡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inscribed mirror|qq=}}, comprising 16 or more specimens.
